        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 4:13PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lilbourn. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Portageville, New Madrid, Lilbourn, Marston, Howardville, Catron, and
North Lilbourn.

This includes Interstate 55 between Mile Markers 34 and 44.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
